  "market_context": "During the 2021 Bitcoin bull run, price surged from a low near $17,618 to a high near $41,958 on the daily chart, establishing a clear uptrend with higher highs and higher lows.",
  "key_observation": "Price pulled back to the Fibonacci zone between 0.5 (50%) and 0.618 (61.8%) retracement levels and reversed upward, confirming the golden zone as a high-probability reversal area.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst selected the Fibonacci Retracement tool from the 'Gann and Fibonacci tools' menu in TradingView.",
    "Step 2: Anchored the Fibonacci tool at the swing low (~$17,618) and dragged it to the swing high (~$41,958) on the BTCUSDT daily chart.",
    "Step 3: Identified key retracement levels: 0.236 ($36,214), 0.382 ($33,214), 0.5 ($29,788), and 0.618 ($26,788) — with exact prices shown on screen in frames f029/f026.",
    "Step 4: Observed that price retraced to the area between the 0.5 and 0.618 levels (the 'golden zone') and reversed upward, validating the retracement as a support zone."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Fibonacci retracement levels—especially the 0.382 to 0.618 zone—are reliable for identifying potential reversal points in strong trends; price rarely drops below 0.618 in healthy bull runs.",
